- content_for :main_content do
  .row-fluid
    .span12
      h2.title1.without_margin DIAGNOSTIC SURVEY
  - if @current_surveys.present?
    - @current_surveys.each do |current_survey|
      -@response_count= current_survey.responses.present? ? current_survey.responses.count : 0
      .row-fluid.without_margin.content-survey
        .span12
          .row-fluid
            .span4
              .content = "Diagnostic for #{current_survey.created_at.strftime('%B %d, %Y')}"
            .span3.text-center
              div Completed Practices
              - if (@response_count<@total_question_total)
                div.type-btn.type-btn-red= "#{@response_count} / #{@total_question_total}"
              - else
                div.type-btn.type-btn-green= "#{@response_count} / #{@total_question_total}"
            .span2.pull-right
              =link_to "VIEW", "#{get_response_status_url(current_survey)}",class: "btn plane-btn"
  - else
    h1.question.without_margin Start a new Diagnostic
    div
      = link_to 'Start Diagnostic', create_survey_path, method: :post, class: 'without_margin'
  .row-fluid
    .span12
      h3.title2.without_margin PREVIOUS DIAGNOSTICS
  -if @completed_surveys.present?
    - @completed_surveys.each_with_index do |completed_survey, i|
      -@response_count= completed_survey.responses.present? ? completed_survey.responses.count : 0
      -if i < 2
        .row-fluid.without_margin.content-survey
          .span12
            .row-fluid
              .span4
                .content = "Diagnostic for #{completed_survey.created_at.strftime('%B %d, %Y')}"
              .span3.text-center
                div Completed Practices
                - if (@response_count<@total_question_total)
                  div.type-btn.type-btn-red= "#{@response_count} / #{@total_question_total}"
                - else
                  div.type-btn.type-btn-green= "#{@response_count} / #{@total_question_total}"

              .span2.pull-right
                =link_to "VIEW", "#{get_response_status_url(completed_survey)}",class: "btn plane-btn"

      - else
        h3 No previous Surveys

  .row-fluid
    .span12
      h3.title2.without_margin NEXT STEPS
      .row-fluid
        .span12
          p.margin-10 The Revenue Grader Serves an early step in strategic planning for revenue growth. It help identify top level areas that require additional focus. The next step is to analyze each of the priorities and develop a specific and detailed plan and timeline. A plan will reflect various dependencies and critical success factors. Revenue Architects can assist in plan development and implementation.

  .row-fluid
    .span12
      h3.title2.without_margin ABOUT REVENUE GRADER

  .row-fluid
      .span8
        p.margin-extra.without_margin Revenue Grader is a Revenue Architects application. It is a diagnostic tool to help businesses leaders rapidly assess revenue performance potencial and develop a prioritized top-level plan - all in minutes. Revenue Grader complements other grader apps by taking a broad and strategic view of the critical elements of revenue performance.
